{{wiktionary | Federal jurisdiction}}
'''Federal jurisdiction''' is the [[jurisdiction]] of the [[federal government]] in any country that uses [[federalism]]. Such a country is known as a [[Federation]].
==Federal jurisdiction by country== All federations, by definition, must have some form of federal jurisdiction, this will commonly include powers relating to international relations and war. Though power for particular actions varies from one federation to another.
